IrcClient

public IrcClient(SocketAddress address,
                 Registrar registrar)
Builds an IRC client that will connect to the specified address, register with the specified registrar, and use a default provider to open socket channels.

Parameters:
address - the address to connect to
registrar - the registrar which will dictate network activity

IrcClient

                 Registrar registrar,
                 SelectorProvider provider)
Builds an IRC client that will connect to the specified address, register with the specified registrar, and use the specified provider to open socket channels.

Parameters:
address - the address to connect to
registrar - the registrar which will dictate network activity
provider - the provider to use for opening socket channels, or null to use the default provider

setDesiredNick

public void setDesiredNick(String desiredNick)
Sets the client's desired nick (nickname). This may or may not be the nick that ends up being used, depending on availability. The argument may be null to choose a nick automatically (which currently means to use the username as nick).

Parameters:
desiredNick - the new value; may be null to choose automatically
See Also:
getDesiredNick()

setUserName

public void setUserName(String userName)
Sets the client's username. If the argument is null, a value will be chosen automatically: the username of the user running the application or, if this cannot be accessed, a randomly-generated value. Because the username is sent on connection and cannot be changed later, make any desired changes before starting.

Parameters:
userName - the new value; may be null to choose automatically
See Also:
getUserName()

setRealName

public void setRealName(String realName)

Parameters:
realName - the new value; may be null to use a blank one

send

public void send(IrcCommand command)
